Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
calculate_didt(25.10)                                    calculate_didt(25.10)

Name
       calculate_didt  - Generates the on-die di/dt information from an exist-
       ing dynamic rail analysis run and saves it in a text file

Syntax
       calculate_didt

       [-help]

       -net_name <net_name>

       -nworst <value>

       -state_directory <dir>

       [-window_steps <value> | -window_size <value> ]

       Generates the on-die di/dt information from an  existing  dynamic  rail
       analysis  run  and  saves it in a text file. This command allows you to
       determine the worst N di/dt events for each bump and for the sum of all
       bumps (vc_sum).

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each calculate_didt parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man calculate_didt

       -net_name <net_name>
              Specifies a net for which the di/dt report is to be generated.

       -nworst <value>
              Specifies  the  number  of  worst windows with the largest di/dt
              values to be reported per bump.

       -state_directory <dir>
              Specifies the name of the state directory where the  information
              on  the  bump-based  di/dt information from the previous run re-
              sides.

       -window_steps <value>
              Specifies the transient time step  size  or  resolution  of  the
              sliding window. The default value is 5.

       -window_size <value>
              Specifies the duration of the sliding window in seconds.

              Note: The -window_size and -window_steps parameters are mutually
              exclusive.  When  both  the  parameters are specified, the -win-
              dow_size parameter takes precedence. If you do not  specify  ei-
              ther  of  the two parameters, the results will be based on a de-
              fault of 5 resolution steps.

Examples
              * The following command generates the on-die di/dt information:

                calculate_didt -nworst  3  -window_steps  10  -net_name  VDD10
                -state_directory ./dynamic_rail/core_125C_dynamic_1

